ion with a radius of 100 - 170 Mpc has a lower density than the cosmic mean.\nFor this reason, the Local Supercluster is not overdense with respect to the\ncosmic mean density. Therefore this local superstructure will not collapse as a\nwhole in the future, but rather fragment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 May 2021 17:24:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-11"}
